Former Real Madrid and Liverpool striker, Michael Owen, has predicted the outcome of the Premier League match-day 35 fixtures taking place this weekend. Everton will host Chelsea in a Premier League tie at Goodison Park on Sunday, while Newcastle United will face Liverpool on Saturday afternoon. Tottenham Hotspur will clash with Leicester City on Sunday afternoon, while West Ham United will host Arsenal on Sunday evening. Providing his predictions, Owen was quoted by BetVictor as saying: Newcastle 2-1 Liverpool
Aston Villa 2-0 Norwich City
Southampton 1-1 Crystal Palace
Watford 1-2 Burnley
Wolves 1-0 Brighton
Leeds United 0-3 Manchester City
Everton 1-1 Chelsea
Tottenham 3-1 Leicester
West Ham 1-1 Arsenal
Man United 1-0 Brentford